[{"text": "Translator: Timothy Covell\nReviewer: Jenny Zurawell", "start": 0.0, "duration": 7.0}, {"text": "I have the answer to a question that we've all asked.", "start": 15.871, "duration": 3.601}, {"text": "The question is,", "start": 19.472, "duration": 1.117}, {"text": "Why is it that the letter X", "start": 20.589, "duration": 2.284}, {"text": "represents the unknown?", "start": 22.873, "duration": 1.998}, {"text": "Now I know we learned that in math class,", "start": 24.871, "duration": 2.967}, {"text": "but now it's everywhere in the culture --", "start": 27.838, "duration": 1.751}, {"text": "The X prize, the X-Files,", "start": 29.589, "duration": 2.801}, {"text": "Project X, TEDx.", "start": 32.39, "duration": 3.923}, {"text": "Where'd that come from?", "start": 36.313, "duration": 1.995}, {"text": "About six years ago", "start": 38.308, "duration": 1.218}, {"text": "I decided that I would learn Arabic,", "start": 39.526, "duration": 2.716}, {"text": "which turns out to be a supremely logical language.", "start": 42.242, "duration": 3.952}, {"text": "To write a word or a phrase", "start": 46.194, "duration": 2.317}, {"text": "or a sentence in Arabic", "start": 48.511, "duration": 1.681}, {"text": "is like crafting an equation,", "start": 50.192, "duration": 2.233}, {"text": "because every part is extremely precise", "start": 52.425, "duration": 2.366}, {"text": "and carries a lot of information.", "start": 54.791, "duration": 2.852}, {"text": "That's one of the reasons", "start": 57.643, "duration": 1.35}, {"text": "so much of what we've come to think of", "start": 58.993, "duration": 1.515}, {"text": "as Western science and mathematics and engineering", "start": 60.508, "duration": 3.819}, {"text": "was really worked out in the first few centuries of the Common Era", "start": 64.327, "duration": 3.322}, {"text": "by the Persians and the Arabs and the Turks.", "start": 67.649, "duration": 3.316}, {"text": "This includes the little system in Arabic", "start": 70.965, "duration": 2.317}, {"text": "called al-jebra.", "start": 73.282, "duration": 1.716}, {"text": "And al-jebr roughly translates to", "start": 74.998, "duration": 3.168}, {"text": "\"the system for reconciling disparate parts.\"", "start": 78.166, "duration": 3.699}, {"text": "Al-jebr finally came into English as algebra.", "start": 81.865, "duration": 4.05}, {"text": "One example among many.", "start": 85.915, "duration": 2.167}, {"text": "The Arabic texts containing this mathematical wisdom", "start": 88.082, "duration": 3.966}, {"text": "finally made their way to Europe --", "start": 92.048, "duration": 1.783}, {"text": "which is to say Spain --", "start": 93.831, "duration": 1.286}, {"text": "in the 11th and 12th centuries.", "start": 95.117, "duration": 2.465}, {"text": "And when they arrived", "start": 97.582, "duration": 1.15}, {"text": "there was tremendous interest", "start": 98.732, "duration": 1.883}, {"text": "in translating this wisdom", "start": 100.615, "duration": 1.734}, {"text": "into a European language.", "start": 102.349, "duration": 1.649}, {"text": "But there were problems.", "start": 103.998, "duration": 2.018}, {"text": "One problem", "start": 106.016, "duration": 1.717}, {"text": "is there are some sounds in Arabic", "start": 107.733, "duration": 2.633}, {"text": "that just don't make it through a European voice box", "start": 110.366, "duration": 2.999}, {"text": "without lots of practice.", "start": 113.365, "duration": 2.267}, {"text": "Trust me on that one.", "start": 115.632, "duration": 1.734}, {"text": "Also, those very sounds", "start": 117.366, "duration": 2.217}, {"text": "tend not to be represented", "start": 119.583, "duration": 1.914}, {"text": "by the characters that are available in European languages.", "start": 121.497, "duration": 3.588}, {"text": "Here's one of the culprits.", "start": 125.085, "duration": 1.814}, {"text": "This is the letter sheen,", "start": 126.899, "duration": 1.884}, {"text": "and it makes the sound we think of as SH -- \"sh.\"", "start": 128.783, "duration": 3.599}, {"text": "It's also the very first letter", "start": 132.382, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "of the word shayun,", "start": 134.984, "duration": 2.432}, {"text": "which means \"something\"", "start": 137.416, "duration": 1.794}, {"text": "just like the the English word \"something\" --", "start": 139.21, "duration": 1.848}, {"text": "some undefined, unknown thing.", "start": 141.058, "duration": 3.286}, {"text": "Now in Arabic,", "start": 144.344, "duration": 1.165}, {"text": "we can make this definite", "start": 145.509, "duration": 1.201}, {"text": "by adding the definite article \"al.\"", "start": 146.71, "duration": 2.148}, {"text": "So this is al-shayun --", "start": 148.858, "duration": 2.602}, {"text": "the unknown thing.", "start": 151.46, "duration": 1.65}, {"text": "And this is a word that appears throughout early mathematics,", "start": 153.11, "duration": 3.303}, {"text": "such as this 10th-century derivation of roots.", "start": 156.413, "duration": 7.2}, {"text": "The problem for the Medieval Spanish scholars", "start": 163.613, "duration": 2.51}, {"text": "who were tasked with translating this material", "start": 166.123, "duration": 2.568}, {"text": "is that the letter sheen and the word shayun", "start": 168.691, "duration": 4.482}, {"text": "can't be rendered into Spanish", "start": 173.173, "duration": 1.95}, {"text": "because Spanish doesn't have that SH,", "start": 175.123, "duration": 2.586}, {"text": "that \"sh\" sound.", "start": 177.709, "duration": 1.297}, {"text": "So by convention,", "start": 179.006, "duration": 1.582}, {"text": "they created a rule in which", "start": 180.588, "duration": 1.666}, {"text": "they borrowed the CK sound, \"ck\" sound,", "start": 182.254, "duration": 4.218}, {"text": "from the classical Greek", "start": 186.472, "duration": 1.748}, {"text": "in the form of the letter Kai.", "start": 188.22, "duration": 2.681}, {"text": "Later when this material was translated", "start": 190.901, "duration": 2.719}, {"text": "into a common European language,", "start": 193.62, "duration": 2.348}, {"text": "which is to say Latin,", "start": 195.968, "duration": 2.05}, {"text": "they simply replaced the Greek Kai", "start": 198.018, "duration": 2.033}, {"text": "with the Latin X.", "start": 200.051, "duration": 2.35}, {"text": "And once that happened,", "start": 202.401, "duration": 1.269}, {"text": "once this material was in Latin,", "start": 203.67, "duration": 2.465}, {"text": "it formed the basis for mathematics textbooks", "start": 206.135, "duration": 3.583}, {"text": "for almost 600 years.", "start": 209.718, "duration": 2.083}, {"text": "But now we have the answer to our question.", "start": 211.801, "duration": 2.018}, {"text": "Why is it that X is the unknown?", "start": 213.819, "duration": 2.781}, {"text": "X is the unknown", "start": 216.6, "duration": 1.823}, {"text": "because you can't say \"sh\" in Spanish.", "start": 218.423, "duration": 3.782}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 222.205, "duration": 2.384}, {"text": "And I thought that was worth sharing.", "start": 224.589, "duration": 2.317}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 226.906, "duration": 3.117}]